O' traveler, hear ye this:
A journey 'tis that doth bring much bliss!
First, visit Kyoto, where temples abound;
Then head to Osaka, with its neon-lit ground.
In Hiroshima, learn of war's atrocity;
And in Nara, behold the Great Buddha's majesty.
Mount Fuji, tallest of all, will take yer breath away;
But beware, for winter brings snow and dismay.
From there, go to Tokyo, city bright;
Therein lies many delights.
Shop till yer drop, eat sushi raw;
Meet friends old and new, and make them drawl.
Finally, return home with fond memories;
Of Japan, never cease to dream.
So plan ye well, and enjoy every day;
For such a journey is truly worthwhile, no delay!

